<SLUG> BC-CUPBIOS22-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Games, players to watch
 &HT;    By Wendy Parker
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ERNIE STEWART
</P>
<P>
   _ Country: United States _ Age: 29.
</P>
<P>
   _ Position: Midfielder. _ Club team: NAC Breda (The
Netherlands).
</P>
<P>
   _ Notes: With speed and a strong scoring touch, Stewart has
developed into a regular role player for the U.S. He has been
bothered by an injury since the Germany match. One of six
European-based U.S. players, Stewart is the son of an American
military man and a Dutch sprinter. He has played his entire career
in The Netherlands. He lived in California for several years as a
child but did not play soccer. Stewart, who had a second-half goal
to clinch a 2-0 upset of Colombia in 1994, has scored 50 goals in
the Dutch pro leagues since 1990.
</P>
<P>
   ALAN SHEARER
</P>
<P>
   _ Country: England. _ Age: 27.
</P>
<P>
   _ Position: Striker. _ Club team: Newcastle United (England).
</P>
<P>
   _ Notes: The captain and rugged leader of England's first World
Cup team since 1990, Shearer scored the first goal in a 2-0 win
against Tunisia. He is a strong and powerful scorer who needs
service to excel, and teamed up well with Teddy Sheringham in the
opener. Without it, he is nearly useless, as evidenced in
Newcastle's loss to Arsenal in the FA Cup finals in May. Shearer
missed most of last season with a bone fracture in his right leg
and hasn't quite fully mended.
</P>
<P>
   TODAY
</P>
<P>
   11:30 a.m.
</P>
<P>
   Colombia vs. Tunisia
</P>
<P>
   (ESPN, Univision)
</P>
<P>
   This may be the end of the line for Colombia, which needs three
points to stay alive in Group G. Coach Hernan Dario Gomez last week
kicked striker Fausino Asprilla off the team for a lack of respect,
then announced his own resignation once the World Cup is over.
Tunisia doesn't have much, but it could be a spoiler by forging a
tie.
</P>
<P>
   3 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   Romania vs. England
</P>
<P>
   (ESPN, Univision)
</P>
<P>
   The best matchup of Group G _ and the two teams likely to
advance. England looked strong in beating Tunisia, but this will be
a stronger challenge from Romania's creative squad, especially
Gheorge Hagi and Adrian Ilie. The new faces for England passed
their first test, but they can't afford to miss on scoring chances
as they did against Tunisia.
</P>
<P>
   Rule book: Getting Fancy
</P>
<P>
   Although players can be called for fouls or be issued cards for
showing their spikes, a bicycle kick is a permissible way to try to
score as long as it doesn't endanger other players. U.S. defender
Marcelo Balboa nearly scored against Colombia in 1994 on a bicycle
kick that makes soccer's perpetual highlight reels. In this World
Cup, Mexico's Cuauhtemoc Blanco squeezed between South Korean
defenders on two occasions by pulling the ball up with both feet
and holding it during his jump. A back-heel pass is another way
attackers try to skirt opposing defenses _ and induce gasps from
the crowd.
</P>
