<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-HOWIE-BIO-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Howie Mandel vital statistics
 &HT;    By Lyle V. Harris
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   _ Born: Nov. 29, 1955
</P>
<P>
   _ Birthplace: Toronto
</P>
<P>
   _ Marital status: Married to wife Terry for 19 years. Three
children: Jackie, 13, Alex, 8, and Riley, 2.
</P>
<P>
   _ Former jobs: Sold rugs door to door, later bought two carpet
stores.
</P>
<P>
   _ First gig: During a 1979 Los Angeles vacation, took a dare to
go on stage at Comedy Store. Got noticed by a Hollywood agent.
</P>
<P>
   _ Big break: Joan Rivers invited him on ``The Tonight Show'' in
1984, which led to 22 subsequent appearances and a role on NBC's
critically acclaimed drama ``St. Elsewhere'' for six seasons.
</P>
<P>
   _ Other work: Headlined 10 cable specials including ``Howie
Mandel on Ice'' for HBO. Comedy concerts at Radio City Music Hall,
Carnegie Hall and Caesar's Palace. Created and starred for eight
seasons on Fox Children's Network's animated ``Bobby's World.''
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
