<HEADLINE>
A CORNUCOPIA OF KOURNIKOVA SITES
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By TOM HOFFARTH  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Forget Wimbledon. Ben Grosman says he's seen enough of Anna
Kournikova.
</P>
<P>
   And he has a Web site dedicated to the 16-year-old Russian
beauty to prove it.
</P>
<P>
   Grosman, a Sydney, Australia, resident who claims the site he
built last July called ``Anna Kournikova: A Rising Star''
(!bold!http://www.annak.com!off!) was the first of its kind,
presently writes on his home page he is ``on the verge of shutting
down'' his cybershrine, in part because he is ``sick of putting
hours of work into this site and finding it constantly
plagiarized.''
</P>
<P>
   But the other reason seems more perturbing to him.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm getting sick of how many other sites are willing to show
pictures of Anna in revealing poses . . . with no respect for
decency or privacy,'' Grosman writes.
</P>
<P>
   So (begin ital)there's(end ital) the person on the 'Net with a
conscious.
</P>
<P>
   Grosman's disenchantment can be traced to the list of Kournikova
sites through a simple search-engine check.
</P>
<P>
   The best example of the Kournikova Internet boom is on the ring
of Kournikova sites
(!bold!http://www.bomis.com/rings/Kournikova!off!). Among the links
to 59 homemade tributes are titles such as:
</P>
<P>
   _ ``Anna, Anna, Anna'';
</P>
<P>
   _ ``The Anna Aphrodisiac'' (which ``unlocks the wonder and
greatness'' of the ``sexiest girls in the world'');
</P>
<P>
   _ ``The Obsessive Anna Kournikova Page'' (which has Kournikova's
name plate pasted over Martina Hingis on a site produced by the
humorous guys at Netmonkey Magazine);
</P>
<P>
   _ ``Scherfi's HOT PICTURES of Anna Kournikova'' (which has moved
and is currently inoperable);
</P>
<P>
   _ ``Anna Kournikova and the Temple of Babes;''
</P>
<P>
   _ ``TonZ of Anna Images'' (more than 600 of 'em);
</P>
<P>
   _ ``The Complete Idiot Annamaniacs Page'' (which includes a
place to take e-mail shots at her reputed boyfriend, Sergei
Fedorov).
</P>
<P>
   And Teri Hatcher thought she had all the young Websurfers' eyes
glued to her.
</P>
<P>
   Grosman is soliciting e-mail responses (bgrosmanhealey.com.au)
to his threat to dismantle his site.
</P>
<P>
   ``This is not Anna's e-mail address,'' he reminds us, ``so don't
e-mail me if all you want to tell Anna is how much you love her.''
</P>
</TEXT>
